==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*τέλος / telos / tel'-os

===Etymology===
*From [[τέλλω]] tellō (to set out for a definite point or goal)

===Noun===
'''τέλος'''

# Properly the point aimed at as a limit, that is, (by implication) the conclusion of an act or state (termination [literally, figuratively or indefinitely], result [immediate, ultimate or prophetic], purpose); specifically an impost or levy (as paid): - + continual, custom, [[end]] (-ing), [[finally]], [[uttermost]]. Compare [[φόρος]].

